     7→ *
     8→ * Description:
     9→ *   Stand-alone micro-service responsible for on-demand texture synthesis.
    10→ *   Exposes a small HTTP/REST surface (with GraphQL overlay handled by the
    11→ *   upstream gateway) enabling clients to request procedurally generated
    12→ *   textures in real time.  
    13→ *
    14→ *   1. Config is read from JSON (environment override: SC_TEXTURE_CONFIG).
    15→ *   2. Robust structured logging (levels, timestamps, source).
    16→ *   3. Graceful shutdown (SIGINT / SIGTERM).
    17→ *   4. Built on libmicrohttpd for tiny HTTP footprint.
    18→ *   5. Implements a simple value-noise generator for demonstration purposes.
    19→ *
    20→ *   Endpoints:
    21→ *     GET /healthz              → {"status":"ok"}
    22→ *     GET /v1/noise?width=..&height=..&scale=..  
    23→ *                                → binary PGM payload (Content-Type: image/x-pgm)
    24→ *
    25→ * Build flags (example):
    26→ *   cc -Wall -Wextra -O2 -DMHD_STATIC -lm -lcjson -lmicrohttpd \
    27→ *      -o texture-service src/main.c
    28→ */
    29→
    30→#include <stdio.h>
    31→#include <stdlib.h>
    32→#include <stdarg.h>
    33→#include <string.h>
    34→#include <signal.h>
    35→#include <time.h>
    36→#include <errno.h>
    37→#include <math.h>
